folder: Humboldt Street & Ten Eyck Street, Brooklyn, NY
original_title: Brooklyn: Humboldt Street - Ten Eyck Street
text:
260-262 Humboldt Stroet, at the N.E. corner of Ten Eyck Street. Also seen is Ten Eyck Street, north side, to Bushwick Ave. Rased buildings are being replaced with new low rent apartments, under the Federal Housing Aot. In the background, at the right, is seen St. Catherine's HIospital.
December 22, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.

Ten Eyck Street (left), north side, between Humboldt Street and Bushwick Ave., across demolition from Stagg Street. In the background at the N.E. c corner of Bushwick Ave., and Ten Eyck Street, is St. Catherine's Hospital.
